question: Will the DPK win the most seats in the South Korean election?
description:
The next legislative elections in South Korea are provisionally scheduled to be held on April 10, 2024.

This market will resolve to "Yes" if the DPK (Democratic Party of Korea) controls a greater number of seats in the National Assembly of the Republic of Korea than any other party after the results of the 2024 South Korean legislative election are finalized. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

If the DPK ties with another party for the most seats, the tied party which comes first in alphabetical order will be considered the winner (e.g., in a tie between the DPK and PPP, the DPK would resolve to "Yes").

If the results of this election aren't known by December 31, 2024, 11:59 PM ET, this market will resolve to “No”.

The primary resolution source for this market will be a consensus of credible reporting. In case of ambiguity, official information from the government of the South Korea and/or information published through the official website (https://korea.assembly.go.kr:447/portalEn/main/main.do) of the National Assembly of the Republic of Korea will be used.

question: Will X remove likes + reposts counter in March?
description:
This market will resolve to “Yes” if X  removes the likes and reposts counter from the feed by March 31, 2024, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise this market will resolve to “No”. 

Both counters need to be removed for this market to resolve to "Yes".

The absence of likes and reposts counter from X's feed due to technical issues, temporary glitches, or third-party interventions will not be considered for the resolution of this market. Only changes implemented as part of a deliberate redesign by X will qualify for market resolution. The likes and reposts counter will be considered removed if it is no longer visible on either desktop or mobile with the English language.

The primary resolution source for this market will be X. However, a consensus of credible reporting may also be used.

question: Kung Fu Panda 4 over $48m opening weekend?
description:
This is a market on how much 'Kung Fu Panda 4' (2024) will gross domestically on its opening weekend. The “Domestic Weekend” tab on https://www.boxofficemojo.com/title/tt21692408/ will be used to resolve this market once the values for the 3-day opening weekend (March 8 - March 10) are final (i.e. not studio estimates).

This market will resolve to "Yes" if ‘Kung Fu Panda 4' (2024) grosses more than $48,000,000 on its 3-day opening weekend. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

Please note, this market will resolve according to the Box Office Mojo numbers under Domestic Weekend for the 3-day weekend (which typically includes Thursday's previews), regardless of whether domestic refers to only the USA, or to USA and Canada, etc.

If there is no final data available by March 18, 2024, 11:59 PM ET, another credible resolution source will be chosen.
